"'''If I Had You'''" is the title of a song written by [[Max Martin]], [[Shellback (songwriter)|Shellback]] and [[Savan Kotecha]]. It was recorded and released as the third single from [[American Idol (season 8)|''American Idol'' season 8]] runner-up [[Adam Lambert]]'s debut album, ''[[For Your Entertainment (album)|For Your Entertainment]]''.
 
==Promotion==
Following the release of the single on May 5, 2010, Lambert performed the song on a series of talk-shows, including ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'' on May 19<ref name="zap2it">{{cite news|title American Idol': Adam Lambert performs 'If I Had You' on 'Ellen'|url=http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2010/05/american-idol-adam-lambert-performs-if-i-had-you-on-ellen.html}}</ref>, and ''[[The Tonight Show with Jay Leno]]'' on May 21.<ref name="mjsbigblog">{{cite news|title Adam Lambert <U+2013> <U+2018>If I Had You<U+2019> <U+2013> Tonight Show with Jay Leno <U+2013> VIDEO |url=http://mjsbigblog.com/adam-lambert-if-i-had-you-tonight-show-with-jay-leno-video.htm}}</ref>

==Music video==
The video premiered June 14, 2010 on [[VH1]] and "takes the late-night wilderness party motif of Jennifer Lopez's classic "[[Waiting for Tonight]]" clip and adds more lasers, guyliner, thrashy dance moves, silver top hats and outrageously spiky shoulder pads."<ref name="billboard">{{cite news|title Adam Lambert Goes Wild in 'If I Had You'|url=http://www.billboard.com/column/viralvideos/adam-lambert-goes-wild-in-if-i-had-you-1004097896.story#/column/viralvideos/adam-lambert-goes-wild-in-if-i-had-you-1004097896.story }}</ref> [[Bryan Barber]] directed the video, which was inspired by Lambert's self-proclaimed "psychedelic" experience at [[Burning Man]].<ref name="billboard"/>

James Montgomery from [[MTV]] describes the video as having "a clearing in the forest, one packed with party people <U+2014> of all races, colors, creeds and proclivities, naturally <U+2014> who are all in the midst of a totally excellent celebration. (Most of said party people are actually Lambert's friends, from his days performing with L.A.'s "Zodiac Show.")"<ref name="mtv">{{cite news|title Adam Lambert's 'If I Had You' Video Frolics In Politics |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1641489/20100614/lambert_adam_american_idol_.jhtml#fbid=VzsGKAIxm89 }}</ref>   Montgomery states the message of the video is "Humanity can, in fact, put their differences aside and just dance."<ref name="mtv"/>

Also making a cameo in the video are Lambert's friends: [[Allison Iraheta]]<ref name="ajcb">{{cite web|title=Adam Lambert<U+2019>s new video for <U+2018>If I Had You,<U+2019> Seacrest<U+2019>s stalker gets two years| author=atlanta journal constitution |url=http://blogs.ajc.com/american-idol-blog/2010/06/15/adam-lamberts-new-video-for-if-i-had-you-seacrests-stalker-gets-two-years/}}</ref> and [[Kesha]].{{fact|date=July 2010}} Additional cameo appearances by Cheeks, Scarlett Cherry, Alisan Porter, Brooke Wendle, Terrence Spencer, Sasha Mallory and [[Cassidy Haley]].

